C. The Receiving Party shall maintain confidentiality of the Disclosed Information for a period of five years following the termination of this Agreement, except in cases where the Receiving Party can provide written evidence that the information:

   a) was known publicly before the disclosure by the Disclosing Party;
   b) becomes publicly available without the receiving party's fault after the disclosure by the Disclosing Party;
   c) was obtained from a source other than the Disclosing Party, who has lawful possession and the right to disseminate such information;
   d) was already known by the Receiving Party before the disclosure by the Disclosing Party; or
   e) was independently developed by the employees or agents of the Receiving Party without using or accessing the information disclosed by the Disclosing Party.
